cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving flow scheduling in data center networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed protocol is designed to be fully distributed, making it scalable to data centers, which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new protocol for flow scheduling, which can be seen as a control problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new scheduling algorithm, which falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of data center networks, which falls under the domain of performance evaluation and optimization.
